    2.2  No ownership rights are transferred to Licensee under this Agreement.  Any rights not expressly granted are reserved by Licensor.

3.  GRANT OF LICENSE
    Subject to full, ongoing compliance with this Agreement and payment of all applicable fees, Licensor hereby grants Licensee a limited, non‑exclusive, non‑transferable, non‑sublicensable, revocable license to:
    (a) download, install, and run one executable copy of the Software in the environment specified in an Order; and
    (b) make a single archival backup copy, provided such copy is not installed or used for productive purposes.

4.  USAGE RESTRICTIONS
    Licensee shall not, and shall not permit any third party to:
    a) copy, distribute, rent, lend, lease, sublicense, or otherwise transfer the Software or any portion thereof;
    b) reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive the source code, algorithms, or underlying ideas of the Software, except to the limited extent (if any) that applicable law expressly permits notwithstanding this restriction;
    c) modify, adapt, translate, or create derivative works based on the Software;
    d) use the Software to provide service‑bureau, time‑sharing, SaaS, hosting, or similar services to third parties without Licensor's prior written consent;
    e) remove or alter any proprietary notices, labels, or marks in the Software;
    f) use the Software in violation of any applicable law, regulation, or export control.

5.  CONFIDENTIALITY & IP PROTECTION
    The Software embodies trade secrets of Licensor.  Licensee shall employ at least the same degree of care it uses to protect its own confidential information (and in no event less than reasonable care) to prevent any unauthorized use, disclosure, reproduction, or distribution of the Software.

6.  SUPPORT AND MAINTENANCE
    Unless otherwise agreed in a separate support agreement, Licensor is under no obligation to provide maintenance, updates, or support services.

7.  LIMITED WARRANTY; DISCLAIMER
