9.  TERM AND TERMINATION
    9.1  Term.  This Agreement is effective on the date Licensee first installs or uses the Software and continues until terminated as set forth herein.
    9.2  Termination for Convenience.  Licensee may terminate this Agreement at any time by destroying all copies of the Software.
    9.3  Termination for Cause.  Licensor may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice if Licensee breaches any material provision and fails to cure within thirty (30) days of notice, or immediately if Licensee becomes insolvent, enters bankruptcy, or attempts an unauthorized transfer of the Software.
    9.4  Effect of Termination.  Upon termination, Licensee must cease all use of the Software, destroy all copies, and certify such destruction to Licensor in writing.  Sections 2, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9.4, 11, 12, and 13 survive any expiration or termination.

10.  EXPORT COMPLIANCE
    Licensee shall comply with all applicable U.S. and foreign export control laws and regulations and shall not export or re‑export the Software to any embargoed country or prohibited end user without the required government licenses.

11.  GOVERNING LAW; JURISDICTION
